cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for building sentence representations without any training, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of pre-trained word embeddings, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on downstream NLP tasks, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the tasks involve image captioning or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) if the tasks involve neural networks.
